<br>
Eadric's got a valid point... with how little hp these PoP mobs have the ability to grab pets that do that kind of damage does make some encounters way easier than I think they were intended to be.  The thing people fail to realize is that charm has always been this powerful.  I never heard a single person complain about me soloing in umbral planes or seru when I was able to pull an aa point in 60-90 minutes.  With PoP everyone is getting exp faster so imo it's not a huge thing that an aa point now takes 40 mins instead of 60.  I just think the problem is that charm soloing has been made a bit too easy so every random chanter who had never charm soloed in their life before is doing it now.  <br>
<br>
